tResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBowman\u0027s layer\u003C/strong\u003E is an acellular, condensed layer of collagen fibers that serves as the basement membrane for the corneal epithelium. It provides structural support and helps maintain corneal shape.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Estroma\u003C/strong\u003E makes up about 90% of the corneal thickness and consists of regularly arranged collagen fibers. \u003Cstrong\u003EDescemet\u0027s membrane\u003C/strong\u003E is the basement membrane of the corneal endothelium. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eendothelium\u003C/strong\u003E is the innermost layer responsible for maintaining corneal hydration. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eepithelium\u003C/strong\u003E is the outermost layer that provides a smooth refractive surface.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFrom anterior to posterior, the five layers of the cornea are: epithelium, Bowman\u0027s layer, stroma, Descemet\u0027s membrane, and endothelium.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The cornea consists of five distinct layers from anterior to posterior: epithelium, Bowman\u0027s layer, stroma, Descemet\u0027s membrane, and endothelium.","Bowman\u0027s layer is a tough layer of collagen fibers that serves as the basement membrane for the corneal epithelium."],"references":["Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Probst, L., \u0026 Tsai, J. (2024). Ophthalmology: Clinical and Surgical Principles. CRC Press","Salmon, J. F. (2024). Kanski\u0027s Clinical Ophthalmology E-Book: A Systematic Approach. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kels BD, Grzybowski A, Grant-Kels JM. Human ocular anatomy. Clin Dermatol. 2015 Mar-Apr;33(2):140-6. doi: 10.1016/j.clindermatol.2014.10.006. PMID: 25704934"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53158"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16324"}},"stemMed